cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with properties of words and their roots, which are central concepts in formal language theory. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a likely category as the paper involves combinatorial and enumerative problems related to words. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper discusses the relation to the theory of codes, which is a central topic in information theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents algorithms for determining Abelian primitivity and discusses the complexity of the problem. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of determining Abelian primitivity and its relation to context-free languages.
